# Deployment discipline

The authoritative workflow is **docs/cursor_skill.md**. Follow it exactly.

## ALL CAPS triggers

When the user types any of these in **ALL CAPS**, execute the corresponding workflow:

- **TEST** → Run `./scripts/skill_test.sh`. Never skip or invent test steps.
- **DEPLOY** → Run `./scripts/skill_deploy.sh` (it runs TEST first, then `./scripts/manage_ha.sh`). Never deploy without TEST passing. Never invent deployment steps. If DEPLOY fails because skill_deploy.sh or other skill scripts crashed/bugged: STOP; propose a patch → require TEST → require CHECKIN (commit the fix) → rerun DEPLOY only after CHECKIN. Do not amend commits or continue deploying in the same run after editing scripts.
- **CHECKIN** → Follow CHECKIN workflow in docs/cursor_skill.md (commit + audit summary).
- **GUARDRAILS** → Restate and enforce repo rules from docs/cursor_skill.md.
- **ROLLBACK** → Provide rollback steps from docs/cursor_skill.md; redeploy only via `./scripts/manage_ha.sh`.
- **PHASE** → Show current maturity posture (gates, flags, what TEST/DEPLOY enforce).

Deploy only via `./scripts/manage_ha.sh`. No other deploy commands.

## Deploy-script failures: no fix-in-place

If DEPLOY fails because **skill_deploy.sh or other skill scripts crashed or bugged**, STOP. Do not fix scripts and continue deploying in the same run. Then: (1) propose a patch, (2) require TEST, (3) require CHECKIN (commit the fix), (4) rerun DEPLOY only after CHECKIN. DEPLOY must not amend commits or continue deploying after editing scripts.

## Required output after TEST / DEPLOY

Always end with this structured block:

```
STATUS:
COMMANDS RUN:
ARTIFACTS:
NEXT ACTION:
```

Fill each line; use PASS/FAIL for STATUS; list exact commands; point to log/artifact paths; give one clear next step.
